		"description": "{html}<div><p>I noticed that HTTPClients crash when downloading files larger\nthan the current free RAM size. This is obviously attributed to the\nfact that Titanium writes the file downloading to a variable\n<strong>before</strong> the data gets written to disk (since the\ndisk writing must be handled onload). A separate method for\ndirectly downloading to disk in order to more efficiently handle\nlarger files would be very useful.</p></div>{html}",
